title: Silver City's Tour of the Gila
Silver City's Tour of the Gila Fun Ride
La Tierra Torture Mountain Bike Race
Pajarito Punishment-Downhill
description: Pajarito Mountain Ski Area is proud to host this year's Central States Cup 2014 Pajarito Punishment Downhill Race and New Mexico Downhill State Championships! This spectator-friendly race will surely challenge you to your limits. It is fast, it's steep, and it's technical, and we know you will enjoy the ride! If the altitude doesn't take your breath away the amazing views around the trails of Pajarito and the National Forrest will. So bring your friends, bring your bike and bring your A game, and join us for this year's best event in the area!
course: The downhill race course will be on a brand new upper course recently built between Bone Crusher and Muy Loco.  The lower half of the course will use the original Muy Loco race course starting at the Muy Loco rock garden.  The finish will go through a new jump or two in the location of the old Jumps Park and will finish in front of the ski lodge deck.
registration: Register online with USAC or onsite.  Onsite registration will not be guarantee a free T-shirt. Pre-reg is encouraged - deadline is 6/6 10pm.
notes: Pracitice Friday afternoon and Saturday morning.  Race Saturday afternoon at 1pm.
directions:
Pajarito Mountain Ski Area is located five miles west of Los Alamos, and is easy to get to from the east or west:

From Santa Fe or Espanola take NM 502 to the Y split east of town, then follow NM 502 through Los Alamos town center.

Either proceed through the LANL security checkpoint on the south side of Omega Bridge, (open to the public - but picture ID required), or take West Road at the traffic light just north of Omega Bridge, which avoids the checkpoint entirely.

From the Jemez on State Road 4, turn left onto NM 501 and then left again onto West Road just before the west checkpoint.

Whichever way you choose, from West Road follow the signs and turn west onto Camp May Road, then drive 3 miles to the ski area.

Click on the map place marker below for detailed directions from any location.

title: Valles Caldera PyroClassic
description: Mark your biking calendar August 3rd for the 1st annual Valles Caldera PyroClassic XC Mountain Bike Race.  Come join the fun for what may be one of the most scenic and challenging  mountain bike races in NM.  The Race courses for Pro/Cat 1, Intermediate, and Beginners will cover the stunning landscape of the Valles Caldera National Preserve, winding through valley meadows and climbing over the flanks of the volcanic upheaval of  11,000 ft. Redondo Peak. The PyroClassic offers race categories for everyone.
course: All races start and finish near the historic Valles Caldera Ranch Headquarters with the beginners doing a 10 mile loop, Intermediates an 18 mile loop, & the Pros/Expert will tackle  the 30 mile Redondo Peak/Alamo Canyon Loop. Climbing on the expert/intermediate course is substantial, with a total ascent of over 2400 ft for the experts, all at an elevation of 8000 ft plus.
registration:
Early Registration is $35/adult, $10 Children (16 and under)  thru July 27.   (This includes the Valles Caldera entrance fee) thru July 27

A USA Cycling race permit is required (one day permits available for $10)     Go to NM Sport Online to Register (https://www.newmexicosportsonline.com)
notes:
Held Under USA Cycling Permit #2014-1845
This Race is part of the New Mexico Off Road Series.
Go to http://nmors.org/ for more information about NMORS
A USA Cycling race permit is required (one day permits available for $10)

New Mexico MTB State Championships - Presented by
Paula Higgins Memorial 2014 Record  Challenge TT
description:
Paula Higgins Memorial
2014 Record Challenge Time Trial
& NM Regional TT Championships (Sunday)
August 31, September 1, 2014
Moriarty, New Mexico
course: Moriarty is 35 miles east of Albuquerque on I-40.  The start is 3 miles south of Moriarty on NM41 (second Moriarty exit-Howard Cavasos Blvd).  Warm up north of the course only.  No warm up on course allowed.
registration:
Online registration only:  $40 solo riders; $45 tandems and TTT.  www.newmexicosportsonline.com  Online registration closes midnight August 28, 2014.  Juniors free if registering online (must have annual license or pay $15 one-day fee.  One day license holders are not eligible for regional awards or National Records.  

Late registration and number pick-up at Sport Systems, 6915 Montgomery Blvd Ne, Albuquerque, NM 87109 on Saturday August 30th Noon to 2pm and at Crossley Park in Moriarty from 5 to 6pm.
notes:
USAC annual license or one-day license required to race. No late fee to register Sunday for a Monday ride.

Awards at Crossley Park in Moriarty approximately 1pm.

Engraved NAMBE platters (Paula Higgins Bill McLain awards) will be presented recognizing the fastest female and male Sunday 40K time trial rides.  MEDALS WILL BE PRESENTED TO THE TOP 5 IN EACH RECORD CHALLENGE AGED CATEGORY.  Certificates with official times will be awarded to all participants.

Regional gold, silver and bronze medals will be awarded in region riders for District Championships.

Race presented by NM Velosport; held rain or shine under USA Cycling event permit pending.
Questions? Email to randyc@swcp.com or 505-440-0603
directions: First rider off at 8:01 am.  Start order 10K, 20K, 40K grouped by age each day.  Sunday start times posted to web and at number pickup on Saturday.  Start times also posted Saturday and Sunday night at Best Western in Moriarty.
